pages.Title: Java QA Automation
pages.Fulltext: Some testers write automation code to improve test efficiency and reduce the amount of manual work required, while others may be motivated by the desire to receive good compensation for working as automation engineers. Regardless of the reasons for writing automation code, it’s important to focus on producing high-quality, reliable, and maintainable code that adds value to the testing process.
